      <p>Exchange-Traded Funds (ETFs) that track the price of gold solve many of the logistical challenges associated with physical ownership. They eliminate the need for secure storage, insurance, and the substantial bid-ask spreads often encountered when buying coins or bars. With a single click, an investor can add targeted gold exposure to their brokerage account.</p>
      <p>However, not all gold ETFs are structured identically. When selecting the right fund for 2025, investors must evaluate critical factors including the fund's expense ratio, its average daily trading volume (liquidity), and its underlying structure (grantor trust vs. ETN). The list below outlines the leading options currently available on the market.</p>
