    <section class="methodology" style="margin-top: 3rem; background: var(--card-bg); padding: 1.5rem; border-radius: 12px; border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">
      <h2>Ranking Methodology</h2>
      <p>When evaluating the best options in the precious metals sector, our framework focuses heavily on structural efficiency and trading costs rather than fundamental company analysis.</p>
      <ul style="padding-left: 1.5rem; margin-top: 1rem;">
        <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;"><strong>Assets Under Management (AUM):</strong> Fund size is a primary proxy for liquidity and institutional acceptance. Larger funds typically offer tighter bid-ask spreads.</li>
        <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;"><strong>Expense Ratio:</strong> For buy-and-hold investors, the management fee is the single largest drag on performance. We highlight funds that offer exposure at the lowest annual cost.</li>
        <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;"><strong>Structure:</strong> We distinguish between physical trusts (which hold actual bullion in vaults) and synthetic products or ETNs (which carry counterparty risk).</li>
        <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;"><strong>Tracking Error:</strong> The ability of the ETF's management team to closely mirror the spot price of gold without significant deviation.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>


